      "QuestionText": "In layered hierarchy as the data packets moved from upper to lower&nbsp; layers ,headers are______.<br>",
      "Options": [
        {
          "OptionId": "A",
          "OptionText": "Added."
        },
        {
          "OptionId": "B",
          "OptionText": "Removed."
        },
        {
          "OptionId": "C",
          "OptionText": "Rearrenged."
        },
        {
          "OptionId": "D",
          "OptionText": "Modified."
        }
      ],
      "Status": 0,
      "Remarks": null,
      "SubjectId": 22,
      "UniqueNodeId": 1183,
      "QuestionTypeId": 0,
      "QuestionId": 70991,
      "Explanation": "Each layer adds its own header to the packet from the previous layer. For example, in the Internet layer, the IP header is added over the TCP header on the data packet that came from the transport layer.",
      "Answer": "A",
